# Twitter Guardrails (canonical: TWITTER_LOOP.md)

Whenever drafting ANY tweet, recap, or social copy for this project:

0. **THE TASTE GATE comes before everything.** Read
   `social_analysis/taste.md` (exemplars + the owner's rejection log) before
   drafting, and check every draft against its kill-list BEFORE showing it:
   no negative/self-deprecating hooks, no stat cards without a story, no
   engineered-clever openers, no paywall apologies, no ad-speak. Kill and
   redraft yourself. When the owner rejects a draft, add a one-line entry to
   the rejection log immediately — that file is how the system learns taste.
   **The executable half is mandatory, and THE BAR IS ELITE, NOT SHIP**
   (raised 7/7 PM — every hero tonight scored SHIP on its first draft and
   still needed 3-6 owner catches to become actually top-1%). Run
   `node scripts/tweetLint.mjs --purpose <REACH|CONVERT|RETAIN> "<text>"` on
   every candidate; below ELITE (>=105 + all 5 gates: authority, proprietary
   punch, not-a-naked-grade, scroll-stopping hook, no critical violation) it
   is NOT a finished draft — iterate, don't show it anyway. Heroes are
   SELECTED, not written: 6-8 different line-1 hooks first (open-loop
   prophecy, first-person stakes, naked number, whale character, countdown),
   lint them, build only from the winner.
   **THEN THE COHERENCE GATE (added 7/7 PM):** run
   `node scripts/dayCoherenceCheck.mjs "<text>"` before showing any draft —
   it reads what ACTUALLY posted in the last 12h (real API data, not your
   memory of the draft — posted text can and does diverge from drafts) and
   flags unpaid grade promises and repeated numbers/angles. Both gates must
   pass before a draft is "finished."
   **THE RECEIPT STACK (added 7/7 — our #1 proven format, per owner's
   bookmarked April tweets at 7.2K-11K impressions, 2-5x baseline):** for any
   pick with 3+ tracked wallets, run `node scripts/walletReceipts.mjs
   <gameKey> <ml|spread|total> [outcome]` BEFORE drafting and build named,
   anonymized (last-4-hex-tag) wallet receipts into the hero — see taste.md
   Part 0 for the exact skeleton. Never hand-type a wallet $ figure.
1. **Verify every number first.** Run `node scripts/socialBrief.mjs` — one
   command: records (yesterday/7d/June 1), the time-bucketed board, ledger
   refresh + report, and the mentions inbox. Never quote a W-L record, unit
   total, or pick that didn't come from it this session. Use the pick's
   `selection` field verbatim.
2. **Build from a FRANCHISE** (TWITTER_LOOP.md G0.5): Morning Board ·
   Decision Window · The Money Moved · Graded · Weekly Ledger. Freestyle only
   if it beats the franchise option. **THE COMBO LAW:** when a fresh win and a
   live pick coexist, they are ONE post — the cashed win is the hook/receipt,
   the live pick is the urgency. Never bury a same-day winner in a subordinate
   clause and never split them into two posts (taste.md, 7/7). **Sound human.** Voice =
   `MY_VOICE_PROFILE.md`. Never the same structure back-to-back. Banned:
   "let's dive in", "game-changer", "delve", default "tail or fade? 🎯"
   closers, 3-emoji rows.
3. **Sell without selling.** Canonical language + TONE RULE: `BRAND_MESSAGING.md`.
   Complete calm sentences — no fragment-stack swagger ("Every L public."), no
   self-conscious mantras. Offer = "the first week is free, grade it yourself";
   never prices or "sign up". Site link ONLY in a ~25-min self-reply, never
   tweet 1. No hashtags. Every draft names the site screenshot to attach.
4. **Prioritize top-tier picks inside 60 min of start.** Picks >60 min out MUST
   carry a natural line-movement reminder: sharp money moves, the site is the
   live truth, picks lock 15 min before start.
5. **Close on a real question** (2026 algo weights replies ~27x likes) and
   recommend a post window + first-30-min reply babysitting.
6. **Research with Firecrawl** (`FIRECRAWL_API_KEY` env secret,
   `https://api.firecrawl.dev/v2/search|/scrape`) for current viral formats
   before big posts; fold findings into `TWITTER_GROWTH_PLAYBOOK.md` (dated).
   **The X API is also live** (MCP server `user-xapi`, or
   `npx -y @xdevplatform/xurl <path>`; authed as @Real_NHL_Savant, user id
   1991513001204281345): use it for engagement truth, the mentions inbox, and
   recent-search reply targets. Credits are pay-per-use — be surgical.
7. **A day's output is a slate, not a tweet** (TWITTER_LOOP.md G7): hero +
   pre-written win/loss grade posts + 3–5 drafted replies under big accounts'
   live betting posts + one new-follower beat. Reply targets are found
   freshest-first (Firecrawl `site:x.com [event] bet`, `tbs:"qdr:n90"` → widen
   to `qdr:h3` → `qdr:d` last). ≤90-min posts get replies; aged-but-viral
   (100K+ views) get quote-tweets. Replies to big accounts are the #1
   out-of-network reach lever at our size.
8. **Target the scored actions** (`ALGO_PSYCH_PLAYBOOK.md` — ground truth from
   X's open-sourced ranker). Every hero names the 2–3 feed actions it's built
   to win (reply / follow_author / photo_expand / share_via_dm / dwell) as
   `algoActions`, passes the negative-signal audit (nothing that earns
   mute/not_interested — polarize the question, never attack a person), carries
   a follow-conversion beat (an open loop that makes following necessary),
   stays in-lane (embedding discipline), and sits ≥2–3h from our previous post
   (author-diversity attenuation).
9. **Log every posted tweet.** When the user says they posted (any phrasing +
   URL), immediately run `node scripts/socialLedger.mjs log --url <url>
   --draft <ready_to_post file> --pick <hero|altN>` (or explicit
   --structure/--mechanic tags for custom copy). Before writing new drafts,
   run `node scripts/socialLedger.mjs refresh` + `report` and let the
   structure/mechanic leaderboards pick the winning shape. Tag every draft
   candidate with structure/mechanic/refTag so logging works.
10. **THE RATCHET — each tweet better than the last.** Every hero MUST carry
    `improvesOn` ("<previous hero id>: the ONE variable changed and why") and
    `prediction` ("OVER|PAR baseline because ..."). Run
    `node scripts/socialLedger.mjs analyze` before drafting: it prints each
    post's OVER/par/UNDER vs the rolling 24h-view baseline, grades past
    predictions, and lists settled posts missing a lesson — write those
    lessons immediately (`socialLedger.mjs lesson --id <id> --text "..."`).
    State the current baseline in the draft summary; the hero's job is to
    beat it. Change one variable per post so wins are attributable.

Full system + phases: `TWITTER_LOOP.md`. Drafts only — never post for the user.
